description:
For sale: $139,900. Location, Location, Location! Lovely views of The Capitol and Downtown Skyline. Historic Building located on Cathedral Hill in the heart of the Cathedral Hill Neighborhood.  Walk to multiple Restaurants, Coffee Shops and Shopping. Downtown, along Summit, Grand and Selby.

Tranquil and private Back Yard to Garden or BBQ.  Off-Street parking - Assigned spot w/Off-Street Guest Parking Spots too.  Easy access location via 94 and 35E. Enjoy an easy St. Paul lifestyle and listen to the Cathedral Bells!

description: For sale: $289,900. Newer townhouse in the heart of Cathedral Hill! Walk to get take out at participating shops along Selby Ave and Coffee from Wee Claddah. Close to several services and restaurants when things return to normal. The townhouse features an open floor plan, updated kitchen real wood hardwood floors, lower level guest room or office, nice sized upper bedrooms and more. Check out the 3D Matterport tour which is attached.

For sale: $240,000. Gorgeous 2 BD / 1 BA Loft; Urban Living at its Finest! This Iconic Architectural Landmark is a Mix of Vintage Elegance & Modern Luxury, offering Tall Ceilings, Original Terrazzo Floors, Huge Windows and a Spacious Open Floor Plan. The Contemporary Airy Unit Features a Walk-In Closet, In-Unit Laundry, and Not to Mention, is Pet-Friendly.  Lowry Lofts are Located in the Heart of Saint Paul. Skyway Connected; Walking Distance to Light Rail, Pazzaluna, Saint Paul Hotel, RiverCentre, The Ordway, Xcel Center, Library, Countless Restaurants and So Much More! Move-In Ready & an Absolute Must-See!

For sale: $165,000. South-facing, one-bedroom unit in the heart of Ramsey Hill. Spacious room sizes andneutral decor make this unit move-in ready. Units are rarely available in this building with a very stable association. Elevator and underground parking. Only a block away from Selby Avenue and all its shops and restaurants.

For sale: $949,000. Intriguing, historic and wonderfully unique! *Easily the most fascinating living space in the Twin Cities*. J.J. Hill's Carriage House, from it's deep arched entryway w/massive copper door, to it's secret, 50x25, courtyard, this 3900 sq ft, loft like multi-level is a must see. Old and new blend perfectly here, original brick and stone walls, full of history,  a full wall of windows, remodeled bathrooms, original tack cabinets, tall bookcases. An inspirational space for the urban dweller!

description: For sale: $135,000. Nice location and close to hiway. Need your magic touch to make it shine again. Sell as is.

For sale: $675,000. This elegant Dutch Colonial is loaded with vintage details, including high ceilings, natural woodwork, and built-ins. The classic kitchen includes an adjoining family room ideal for cozy evenings. Upstairs, you'll find three generously-sized bedrooms, including a master suite with decorative fireplace and great closet space. You'll also appreciate the newer plumbing, windows, drain tile, sump pump, and more. Easy access to restaurants, shops, and downtown!

For sale: $950,000. Cass Gilbert designed, the Lightner-Young Mansion is a stately feature of the bluff side of Summit Avenue. Breathtaking views of downtown and the river valley can be taken in from 3 decks! The residence occupies the top two floors of the building and also has an additional apartment accessible by a private elevator. The main level features great entertaining space-lovely kitchen with Wolf and Sub Zero flows into the dining room with soaring vaulted ceilings and views from two decks. Beyond, find a large living room with a fireplace flanked by built-in bookshelves. Main level bedroom is currently set as a den/library. As you make your way up the open staircase, the huge stained glass skylight draws your eye to an expansive third deck off of the top floor. Master bedroom with ensuite and a third bedroom with 3/4 bath complete level. The garden level apartment features a wet bar, laundry and 3/4 bath - perfect for in-law unit or special guest space! Two car garage completes this property.

For sale: $249,900. Rare 5 bed 2 bath 2 story with loads of potential. The home features 4 bedrooms and laundry on the second level. The main floor features the 5th bedroom and a 3/4 bath. With nearly 2,000 square feet there is room to grow in this property. The home features a massive kitchen and a huge master bedroom. The two car garage is oversized and has a loft for storage. Great  opportunity to make this home your own.

Spot on attention to natural light creates a lovely juxtaposition between dark stone exterior and BRIGHT interior, quite magical! Open and airy spaces are perfectly balanced with private wings and nooks, all flooded with natural light. description: For sale: $1,950,000. Experience "Country Club" living in the middle of St Paul with this historic gem! Artistically designed, the home and expansive grounds -complete with immaculate gardens and expansive pool area- create a private, park-like setting  in the middle of the city. description: For rent: $1,790. Available now!! Live in one of the coolest historic buildings in Cathedral Hill - The Commodore! This incredibly clean and bright condo has two bedrooms and two baths with a floor plan that offers privacy. Freshly updated to reflect what renters are looking for today with the convenience of being close to downtown STP, I94, 35E, and Grand/Selby avenues to walk too. One heated underground garage spot comes with the condo, as well as cable, internet, water, garbage.

Recently sold: $330,000. Fabulous two story home with original charm right off of West 7th! Enjoy 10' ceilings, beautiful hardwood floors, abundant sunlight, and much more. This home was completely redone in 2015 from the studs in, including new mechanicals, Pella Windows and appliances! Open spaces will allow family and friends to flow easily through the living areas. Main floor lays claim to powder room, mudroom, formal DR, and 2 living rooms! Four bedrooms are grouped upstairs with great storage space, a laundry room, and a unique reading nook along the hallway. Take a walk to many nearby places such as Degidio's for Italian food or Bad Weather Brewing to sit on the patio! An easy commute to downtown, popular shops along Grand Ave, or a short drive to the Intl. Airport. Don't miss your chance to call this home!

Recently sold: $355,000. Premier Summit Avenue location. Classic Saint Paul Summit Avenue 2 bed plus den condo located in historically significant 1898 Clarence Johnston designed luxury apartment building. Top floor, elegantly proportioned rooms with 10ft ceilings and original details including decorative fireplace, hardwood floors, built-in buffet, columns, moldings and doors. Custom architect designed kitchen and bathroom renovation with high end finishes and appliances. French doors leading from living room to private tree top deck. In-unit laundry. description: For sale: $999,500. St Paul's newest luxury custom build opportunity Irvine Park Estates!  Three homesites/lots walking distance to all West 7th and downtown have to offer. Breathtaking views of the Mississippi river valley from the two tiered deck systems. You choose your floor plan and finishes, this is truly a custom build opportunity! This Neo-classic style home inspired by the classical architecture of ancient Greece and Rome is one of many options our Architect can custom design for you. Options include: 3 car attached heated and insulated garage. Handmade custom kitchen cabinets, vanities, built-ins and trim finished on site.  Master on main or all bedrooms on upper level if you prefer!  We can even incorporate an elevator to make this home truly timeless for a forever home!!   Don't miss out on this unique and exclusive opportunity to custom build on one of these three lots surrounded by other historic St Paul homes!
Recently sold: $205,000. 1885 build with 2014 renovation. All major systems updated in 2014. Must see single story in great neighborhood. Popular dining destinations abound the iconic west 7th area.

Recently sold: $216,363. Sparkling 3-Bedroom gem is brimming with charm and great updates! The sun-drenched Front Porch welcomes you. Step into the Living Room to find lovely hardwood floors, bright windows, and a breezy ceiling fan. Enjoy quiet dinners or large holiday feasts in the spacious Formal Dining Room. The Kitchen offers sleek white cabinetry, tiled backsplashes,  and classic hardwood floors. The main floor Bedroom would be ideal as a Den or Home Office. Two generous Bedrooms can be found on the upper level + great storage too! Lower level Laundry Room and space for your hobbies or workbench. Your car will be protected from the elements in the Garage. Updates include new furnace and roof in 2009; new front door and 6 windows on the main level in 2011; drain tile in lower level in 2014; new asphalt parking in 2015. The following are all new in 2019: garage service door, back screen door, front walk, storm windows in porch, freshly painted interior and new carpet. All the work has been done, move right in!

Recently sold: $164,900. Beautiful and spacious remodeled 2 bedroom condo at The Gallery!!!  White solid maple cabinets, quartz counter tops, white trim and doors, stainless steel appliances and high end flooring!  HOA dues cover cable and internet! Electric bill averages $40 a month! Conveniently located to experience ALL that Downtown Saint Paul has to offer: Green Line, Lund's, bars, restaurants, theaters, CHS Field and the Xcel Energy Center!  Pet friendly building!!!

Recently sold: $157,300. Wonderful home in West 7th neighborhood! This home features new laminate flooring, new carpeting, and freshly painted walls. Enjoy a spacious living room w/tall ceilings, lots of windows allowing daylight to stream through, and a built-in entertainment area. Travel around the corner to the eat-in kitchen and find a great space to prepare your favorite recipes! SS appliances, new backsplash, and great storage are just some features that will catch your eye. Weekend breakfasts can easily be served here w/the addition of a center island. Down the hallway you will find a den perfect to use as a home office! Main floor bathroom is just off of the living room. Traveling to the upper level the two bedrooms sit on the front and back of the home; each is generous in size and lay claim to large closets. The backyard is fully fenced and lush w/green grass! Your four-legged family members will love exploring thanks to full fencing. A great location close to restaurants, shops, downtown, and much more!

description: Recently sold: $238,500. Open concept kitchen - living room; and newer windows throughout offer easy living. Originally three bedrooms on the main level, the owner converted 2 bedrooms to a larger master bedroom with a sliding door to a huge 3 season porch. A new maple vanity graces the main floor bathroom. The kitchen bar can be left as it is or detached from the wall easily for a kitchen/dining room (on consistently ceramic flooring in both kitchen and dining area). Lower level has non-conforming bedroom (lacks egress window), family room, nice 3/4 bath, and drain tile. Gas fireplace, plus furnace provide lots of warmth in lower level all year round. Mechanics and woodworkers - the garage is insulated and heated.

description:
Recently sold: $377,000. Fully Furnished home in GREAT location -- Summit/University/Cathedral Hill. 1000 + sq/ft. Relocating to St Paul? Move into our cheerful, light filled, south facing home that includes 2 bedrooms, 1 bathroom, a lofted living room, a wood burning stove, a separate dining area and a spacious kitchen. The home was recently updated with VOC free Benjamin Moore paint and new wood floors. We encourage sustainable living and will provide a compost system and space to garden, hang your wash outside and tool storage. Tenants pay electric and gas utilities. You can't beat the location. Within 3 blocks you can stroll to the Mississippi Market Natural Food Coop (www.msmarket.coop), 3 coffee shops, 5 restaurants, bakeries, home stores, gift stores and 2 pocket parks. There is another urban living district 4 blocks south, on Summit and Grand Avenues. Here you will find numerous shops, restaurants, a hardware store and more. You can reach the Green Line train to Minneapolis in a mile and the Capitol building is only 2 miles away. Some favorite eateries within blocks include: French Hen Cafe (www.frenchhencafe.com), Louisiana Cafe (www.newlouisianacafe.com), Great Harvest Bread Company (www.stpaulbread.com), Nina's Coffee Cafe (www.ninascoffeecafe.com) and WA Frost (www.wafrost.com) and Sweeny's Salon (www.sweenyssalon.com)

Universities and Elementary Schools nearby include:

Mitchel Hamline School of Law, .8 miles
Saint Paul College, 1 mile
Concordia University, 1.7 miles
Macalaster College, 2.6 miles
Barack and Michelle Obama Elementary, .3 miles
JJ Hill Montessori, .9 mile

Additional Amenities included:

* Wi-Fi
* Water and Sewer utilities
* Waste and Recycling pick up
* Air conditioning and forced air heat
* Free laundry in building
* Snow shoveling and lawn care
* Big yard and attractive fence
* Easy to clean hardwood and tile floors throughout
* All furnishings. Everything you view in the pictures and more including desk organizers and games
* Household goods from linens to soap
* King bed in master bedroom
* 2 twin beds in second bedroom
* Pets o.k. based on meeting with landlord and or references. Pet Deposit required
* New gas cooking stove
* Microwave
* Well equipped kitchen -- dishes, pots and pans, waffle maker, blender and more
* Starter pantry with organic staples from spices, oil and vinegar to Annie's Mac and Cheese
* Optional monthly social gathering with downstairs tenant to foster community
* Responsive landlord -- Contact Sonya Newenhouse for application. $2000 deposit.

Owner pays for Wifi, Waste and Recycling, Snow and Lawn Care.

AGENTS ONLY: To schedule a PRE-MLS showing for your buyer, please email caneill@CBBurnet.com or call Chris Neill at 612-799-0017 for access and info. 

Wow! This gorgeous 2 bed / 2 full bath condo has stunning views, plenty of space, and great luxuries such as the 3-sided fireplace and built-in bar area! This condo boasts an eat-in kitchen with gleaming hardwood floors, granite countertops, and stainless steel appliances! The formal living room with built-in bar area and wine refrigerator is perfect for hosting, or you and your guests can relax in the family room that has huge windows and a 3-sided fireplace to make you feel cozy and at home!  The master suite has an ideal walk-in closet, private full bath with double sinks and separate tub and shower! The excellent location is in the heart of downtown Saint Paul, but has ample parking, and is surrounded by the natural beauty of Upper Landing Park and the Mississippi National River and Recreation Area!   Bonuses include, in-unit laundry, multi-use office/bedroom space, rooftop patio with remarkable view of Saint Paul skyline and Mississippi River, underground heated garage, and attached amenities such as Caribou Coffee & Anytime Fitness!
